      "segment_text": "    be the first choice for session-bound pairs.\n  - If worker progress reveals new edge cases, tests, polish, or scope\n    boundaries, ask the worker to propose must-have vs follow-up criteria.\n  - After a worker proposes separated criteria, use `scripts/workerctl\n  criteria-plan`\n    to draft reviewed criteria commands, then run only the commands you agree\n  with.\n  - Record useful criteria with `scripts/workerctl criteria`.\n    Examples:\n    - `scripts/workerctl criteria codex-smoke-task-smoke-20260519083508 --add\n  --criterion \"...\" --source worker_proposed --status proposed`\n    - `scripts/workerctl criteria codex-smoke-task-smoke-20260519083508 --add\n  --criterion \"...\" --source manager_inferred --status accepted`\n    - `criterion_id=$(scripts/workerctl criteria codex-smoke-task-smoke-\n  20260519083508 --add --criterion \"...\" --source worker_proposed --status\n  proposed | python3 -c 'import json,sys; print(json.load(sys.stdin)\n  [\"affected_criterion\"][\"id\"])')`\n    - `scripts/workerctl criteria codex-smoke-task-smoke-20260519083508\n  --satisfy \"$criterion_id\" --evidence-json\n  '{\"command\":\"...\",\"status\":\"pass\"}'`\n  - Use `worker_proposed` for criteria that came from the worker.\n  - Use `manager_inferred` for criteria inferred from manager config, cycle\n    evidence, or the manager's own inspection; `manager_config` is not a valid\n    criteria source.\n  - Before finishing, compare worker receipts/verification against accepted\n  open criteria.\n  - Communicate with the worker only through workerctl session/task commands.\n  - Do not edit project files unless the user explicitly asks this manager\n    session to change workerctl itself.\n\n\n\u26a0 Heads up, you have less than 25% of your 5h limit left. Run /status for a\n  breakdown.\n\n\u2022 Starting MCP servers (2/3): posthog (1s \u2022 esc to interrupt)\n\n\n\u203a Run /review on my current changes\n\n  gpt-5.5 medium \u00b7 ~/Desktop/codex-terminal-manager \u00b7 main",
